text: Duran Creek (also spelled Duren Creek) is a stream in Benton County in the U.S. state of Missouri. It is a tributary of Cole Camp Creek.Lakeview Heights, MO, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1983 Duran Creek was named after Mannen Duren, an early settler. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Benton County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
title: Duran Creek
